# MAS BADGES · Netlify redirects
#
# Host canonicalisation is enforced in-app (App.tsx HostGuard) for known
# public/portal paths. This file handles the edges Netlify can catch at the
# CDN before the SPA loads:
#   1. Bare masbadges.org -> www.masbadges.org (marketing home).
#   2. Any *.netlify.app preview -> single canonical host so social crawlers
#      and search engines see one origin.
#   3. SPA fallback: hand every remaining route to /index.html so React
#      Router owns the URL.

# 1 · Apex -> www (301, permanent, preserves path and query)
https://masbadges.org/*    https://www.masbadges.org/:splat    301!

# 2 · Netlify preview / *.netlify.app -> www (only affects the production
#     alias, not deploy previews and branch deploys which use their own hosts)
#     Comment this rule out if you rely on the production Netlify subdomain
#     for anything besides certificate provisioning.
# https://*.netlify.app/*   https://www.masbadges.org/:splat    301!

# 3 · SPA fallback for both hostnames
/*    /index.html    200
